The healthcare and insurance company disclosed Friday that it expects to close the sale in the first half of next year and record a mostly non-cash $7 billion charge as a result, largely from the impact of foreign currency translation losses.

[Headline]: UnitedHealth Is Selling Operations in Brazil. That Will Impact Earnings Next Year.
[Summary]: UnitedHealth Group  stock was edging higher early Friday after the health insurer shared a business update ahead of its earnings report on Jan. 12.  In a securities filing Friday, the company said it has agreed to sell its operations in Brazil to a private investor.  The sale — set to close in the first half of next year — is expected to record a charge of about $7 billion and will impact the company’s 2024 net earnings outlook.
